The microstructure of CDs was determined by using TEM. As TEM image of CDs (Fig. 1
                        ) illustrated, CDs are individually spherical in shape and possess great dispersibility without agglomeration. In addition, CDs show a narrow size dispersion, and the mean diameter is 13.40 nm in aqueous solution analyzed by DLS in Fig. S2. While, the average diameter of CDs is 1.41 nm from TEM in Fig.1. it is known that the CDs diameter by DLS is hydration particle diameter and it is usually larger than the diameter detected by TEM. So, the result is reasonable. Meanwhile, the XRD data of CDs is shown in Fig. 2
                        A, the peak of 22.7° [40] is ascribed to the graphitic structure.
